Introduction:

To me, happiness is eating dessert, having a good sleep, reading some books, staying with my family, lying on the beach and so on. Its easy to tell why Im happy since it is one of the most common feeling. Now Im going to learn happiness of other people. Im using the dataset called HappyDB, which is a corpus of 100,000 crowd-sourced happy moments. I wonder the difference of what make people happy between groups.

Data Analysis

This is a brief review of our data. Both two variable in each plots shows the data is large enough to analyse.

From this wordcloud, the most frequent words participators mentioned are friend, day, time. These words cant tell us much information because they are common words in daily life. Then comes family, home, enjoyed, dinner and so on. These are also common since everyone owns these. Words in lighter color contains cat, birthday, school, movie. These refers to small groups of people, or a specific time period Lets get further information by dividing these participators.

First, We divided the dataset into two groups, male and female. I listed 20 words with the higher frequent by order. If theres no difference between these groups, both the trend would look smooth. However,from this histogram, I find the bar of son and daughter move towards positive, meanwhile played, game move towards negative side. It shows that men and women have different focuses.

Heres the detailed information. These two plots lists the highest frequent words corresponding to female and male. For female, Son, family, daughter are more frequently talked, while for male, these key words are less frequently talked than played and watched.

This plot further indicates that theres clear distinction between male and female about pleasure. Key words near the red regression line are the ones without tendency. But the outliers which are far away from the line, indicate a tendency, such as video, won, laugh, surprise.

Some outliers for male: ate purchased project promotion video girl local team fixed bonus dollars bike win match emotional beat basketball beer wellbeing .
Some outliers for female: laugh hard smile children proud child sitting hug cute hear flowers care ready .

According to the dataset, achievement and affection are pointed out by more people. It shows that female enjoy affection more than male do, while male likes achievement. Theres no huge difference between two groups on other category. I wonder what other factors may result this difference.

I plot the affection of age on topics for male and female separatly. First look at male, theres simple trend on each category as age increases, especially affection. The proportion of elderly get happiness from affection is much more than younger people. However, for female, it is interesting that the trends for achievement and affection look like two parabola. Female has lowest achievement and enjoy_the_moment and highest affection from happiness in their 30s, compared to other age groups.

The proportion of married people exceed single people from 26-30 to 31-40. So it is reasonable to guess that marital status is possibly related to the vertex of parabola.

For female, after married, the bar of achievement decreases. Also the bar of affection has a huge increases, which corresponds to the peak in the previous plot on group 31-40.

From this plot, we can see that affection and enjoy_the_moment are grouped together, which are mentioned more times than others.

It confirms that affection and enjoy_the_moment are a group. In addition, people from 22-40 are grouped together. It shows that age has more important influences in this clustering than gender.
